The 93-year-old will be buried at the Mowbray Muslim cemetery on Sunday afternoon. CAPE TOWN - Galiema Haron, the wife of anti-Apartheid activist Imam Haron, has died this morning, almost exactly 50 years since the cleric died while in detention. The 93-year-old will be buried at the Mowbray Muslim cemetery on Sunday afternoon. The news comes days after Imam Haron's gravesite at the same cemetery was declared a provincial heritage site. The Al-Jamia Masjid in Claremont has also been declared a provincial heritage site.